ption%3EFl%C3%A1via%20Fayet-Moore%2C%20better%20known%20as%20Dr.%20Flav%2C%20is%20a%20space%20nutritionist%20who%20partnered%20with%20SpaceX%20and%20NASA%20to%20study%20how%20oyster%20mushrooms%20grow%20in%20orbit.%3Cp%3EFOODiQ%20Global%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EFl%C3%A1via%20Fayet-Moore%20is%20a%20nutrition%20scientist%20studying%20how%20oyster%20mushrooms%20grow%20in%20space.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20partnered%20with%20NASA%20and%20SpaceX%20to%20send%20the%20first%20fungi%20into%20orbit%20on%20a%203-day%20flight.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EFayet-Moore%20says%20fungi%2C%20due%20to%20their%20nutritional%20benefits%20and%20fast%20growth%20cycle%2C%20may%20help%20us%20get%20to%20Mars.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Fl%C3%A1via%20Fayet-Moore%2C%20a%20nutrition%20scientist%20and%20the%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20FOODiQ%20Global%2C%20a%20nutrition%20research%20company.%20On%20a%20March%2031%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspacex-history-biggest-moments-elon-musk-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ESpaceX%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20flight%20departing%20out%20of%20Florida%2C%20the%20company%20plans%20to%20send%20their%20mushroom%20experiment%20to%20space%20as%20part%20of%20a%20partnership%20with%20NASA%20and%20SpaceX.%20This%20essay%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20two%20years%20ago%2C%20I%20started%20thinking%20that%20we%20should%20try%20growing%20mushrooms%20in%20space.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20researching%20the%20nutritional%2C%20culinary%2C%20and%20health%20benefits%20of%20fungi%20for%20the%20past%20seven%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20a%20lot%20of%20cool%20things%20about%20mushrooms%20that%20make%20them%20well-suited%20to%20the%20task.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20mushrooms%20grow%20really%20rapidly.%20I%20explain%20to%20everyone%20and%20it%20blows%20their%20mind%20to%20learn%20that%20sweet%20brown%20mushrooms%20%E2%80%94%20those%20little%20cap%20mushrooms%20you%20see%20at%20the%20store%20%E2%80%94%20and%20portobellos%20are%20the%20same%20mushrooms.%20They're%20the%20same%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-you-cant-overcook-mushrooms-2016-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efungi%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20portobellos%20are%20harvested%20just%20two%20days%20later%20than%20the%20little%20ones.%20They%20grow%20that%20fast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20end-to-end%20crop%20cycle%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmushrooms-could-be-the-secret-to-a-better-smartphone-battery-2015-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emushrooms%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20about%2045%20days.%20That's%20not%20very%20long%2C%20so%20we're%20not%20waiting%20190%20days%20to%20harvest%20something%20like%20other%20plants.%20They%20also%20require%20minimal%20resources%2C%20like%20water.%20They%20don't%20need%20sunlight%20to%20synthesize%20because%20they're%20not%20plants%2C%20and%20they%20can%20thrive%20in%20really%20small%20spaces.%20Not%20to%20mention%2C%20they're%20very%20resilient%2C%20and%20they're%20really%20good%20at%20surviving%20different%20changes%20in%20their%20environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20they're%20entirely%20edible.%20You%20can%20consume%20the%20whole%20mushroom%20so%20there's%20no%20waste.%20So%20let's%20say%20you%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstarted-home-garden-no-experience-save-money-on-groceries-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egrow%20tomatoes%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20you%20don't%20eat%20the%20whole%20plant%20so%20there's%20plant%20waste%2C%20and%20you've%20got%20to%20figure%20out%20what%20to%20do%20with%20that.%20The%20beauty%20of%20mushrooms%20is%20that%20when%20they%20decompose%2C%20you%20can%20reuse%20the%20inevitable%20plant%20waste%20as%20part%20of%20the%20substrate%20needed%20for%20them%20to%20grow%2C%20so%20they%20help%20close%20that%20loop%20in%20agriculture.%20If%20you've%20ever%20gone%20to%20a%20nursery%20and%20got%20mushroom%20compost%20that's%20treated%20with%20mushroom%20substrate%2C%20you%20know%20it%20is%20really%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fdiet-nutrition%2Fmushroom-benefits%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enutrient-rich%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20it's%20great%20for%20growing%20more%20plants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20most%20importantly%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnasa-reduction-in-force-plans-department-closures-doge-firings-trump-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENASA%3C%2Fa%3E%20prioritizes%20whole%20foods%20over%20supplements%2C%20because%20there's%20a%20benefit%20to%20eating%20whole%20foods.%20In%20nutrition%20science%2C%20you%20know%20that%20when%20you%20start%20supplementing%2C%20it's%20not%20the%20same%20effect%20in%20the%20body%20as%20nature%20intended%20with%20the%20combination%20of%20nutrients.%20So%20fungi%20are%20a%20whole%20food%20source%20of%20very%20high%20nutrition%3B%20they've%20got%20nutrients%20found%20across%20our%20food%20groups%2C%20from%20grains%20to%20vegetables%20to%20nuts%20and%20seeds%20to%20fish%20and%20meat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAstronauts%20are%20given%201000%20IUs%20of%20vitamin%20D%20daily%20to%20maintain%20bone%20health%2C%20and%20mushrooms%20can%20naturally%20produce%20vitamin%20D%20when%20they're%20exposed%20to%20UV%20light%2C%20just%20like%20humans%20can.%20So%20basically%2C%20we%20can%20get%20100%25%20of%20our%20vitamin%20D%20requirements%20with%20just%20100%20grams%20of%20mushrooms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20also%20research%20showing%20that%20when%20you%20add%20mushrooms%20to%20a%20meal%2C%20you%20can%20add%20less%20salt%2C%20which%20is%20really%20important%20because%2C%20in%20space%2C%20having%20too%20much%20sodium%20exacerbates%20the%20amount%20of%20calcium%20that's%20leached%20from%20the%20bone.%20So%20it's%20a%20counter-measure%20to%20have%20a%20lower-sodium%20diet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20if%20all%20that%20weren't%20enough%2C%20what's%20%3Cem%3Ereally%3C%2Fem%3E%20cool%20about%20mushrooms%20is%20that%20they're%20very%20rich%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fkitchen%2Fumami%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eumami%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That's%20the%20fifth%20basic%20taste%2C%20like%20sour%2C%20sweet%2C%20salty%2C%20or%20bitter%20%E2%80%94%20and%2C%20unlike%20the%20other%20flavors%2C%20umami%20seems%20to%20be%20well%20retained%20in%20a%20space%20environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20just%20like%20an%20airplane.%20Have%20you%20ever%20ordered%20a%20wine%20on%20a%20flight%20and%20then%20tried%20the%20same%20one%20after%20landing%3F%20It%20tastes%20different.%20Everything%20is%20dampened.%20It's%20the%20lower%20humidity%20and%20higher%20cabin%20pressures%20that%20change%20the%20palatability.%20Not%20with%20mushrooms%2C%20you%20still%20get%20that%20umami%20flavor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20where%20it%20gets%20particularly%20interesting%20for%20long-haul%20space%20flights%2C%20like%20the%20kind%20we'll%20need%20to%20take%20to%20get%20to%20Mars.%20Can%20you%20imagine%20eating%20thermostabilized%2C%20dehydrated%20food%20for%20five%20years%3F%20I%20can't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20important%20thing%20about%20food%20is%20nutrition%2C%20sure%2C%20but%20food%20is%20so%20much%20more%20than%20that.%20It's%20a%20fundamental%20part%20of%20our%20culture%20and%20survival%20and%20mental%20health.%20At%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fastronauts-best-photos-from-space-station-this-year-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInternational%20Space%20Station%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20astronauts%20love%20coming%20together%20at%20the%20dinner%20meal%20and%20eating%20and%20exchanging%20food.%20It's%20nostalgic%2C%20but%20it's%20also%20a%20comfort.%20They're%20isolated%2C%20they're%20far%20away%20from%20home.%20So%20food%20becomes%20a%20way%20to%20connect%20with